org.odejava.xith3d
Class OdejavaToXith3D

java.lang.Object
  org.odejava.xith3d.OdejavaToXith3D
public class OdejavaToXith3D
extends Object

This class creates Xith3D objects automatically based on Odejava objects.

User's may let this class automatically select what kind of Xith3D shapes are used for each Odejava Geom's, or define their own shape for each Geom. It's also possible to use default shapes per Odejava object and change only it's appearance or map user defined TransformGroup (composite shapes) against Geom. Mapping Odejava Geom's to user defined shapes, appearances or TransformGroups are done by Geom's name.

Usage example:

1. Define your own appearances, shapes or TransformGroups (optional)

  • If nothing is set, then default shapes and appearances are used.

    • 2. Create Xith3D objects with createTransformGroups

  • Result's can be queried with methods getBodyTransformGroup() and getGeomTransformGroup(). Note that Odejava Geom's are unmovable static objects and Body objects are also Geom's but they have dynamic position and orientation. Xith3D application can then add resulting TransformGroup objects into scene e.g. by using addTransformGroupToScene conviniency method.

    • 3. Modify your application's rendering process

  • Update Odejava related TransformGroups by calling updateBodyTGs because Odejava is constantly updating TransformGroup's position and orientation.

    • You can scale objects visually using setScale() method.

    Complete usage example can be found from org.odejava.xith3d.test.CarExample class.

    Author:
    Jani Laakso E-mail: jani.laakso@itmill.com

    Method Detail

    createTransformGroups

    public void createTransformGroups(List odejavaGeoms)

    Create Xith3D transform group lists based on given Odejava geometry list. Call this method before starting to step forward your Odejava simulation. Results can be obtained with getBodyTransformGroup() and getGeomTransformGroup().

    Every Odejava geometry is created as shape(s) in Xith3D. You can add your own transformgroup or shape to any Geom with addUserTransformGroup() or addUserShape() methods. Otherwise default shapes are used provided by this class. Default shapes are constructed automatically based on Odejava's geometry data like sphere's radius, length of the box's sides or trimesh vertices. Note that only Box, Sphere and TriMesh shapes are supported, if you have other type of Geoms then you must use your own shape.

    Mapping Geoms to renderable Xith3D objects goes following:

  • If userDefinedTransformGroup map contains Geom's name as an key, then user's transformGroup will be used for rendering the Geom.
  • If userDefinedShapes map contains Geom's name as an key, then user's shape will be used for rendering the Geom.
  • If no match is found, then default shapes will be used for rendering the Geom.

    • Geoms that have Body are dynamic, their position and orientation may change during Odejava simulation step. If Geom is attached into Body, then it will be added to this classes bodyTransformGroup list

    Geoms that have no Body are static (unmovable). If Geom is not attached into Body, then it will be added to this classes geomTransformGroup list.

    Parameters:
    odejavaGeoms - contains list of Odejava geoms to be added into result lists.
    Returns:

    Supported Geom classes:

  • GeomSphere
